I"*<h1 id="problem">Problem</h1>
<p><img src="/assets/problem2.png" alt="problem2" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>On number line, when the current point is X, the next movement is one of X+1, X-1, 2*x. It takes 1 second for each movement.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Given the current point X and target point D, print out minimum seconds required for reaching to the target point.
(0 &lt;= X, D &lt;= 100,000)</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Example Input: 5 17</li>
      <li>Example Output: 4</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>source</strong>
â€œ K-MOOC í—ˆì¬í•„ êµìˆ˜ë‹˜ì˜ &lt;ì¸ê³µì§€ëŠ¥ì„ ìœ„í•œ ì•Œê³ ë¦¬ì¦˜ê³¼ ìë£Œêµ¬ì¡°: ì´ë¡ , ì½”ë”©, ê·¸ë¦¬ê³  ì»´í“¨íŒ… ì‚¬ê³ &gt; ê°•ì¢Œì˜ ê³¼ì œ1 ì¤‘(http://www.kmooc.kr/courses/course-v1:SKKUk+SKKU_46+2020_T1)â€</p>

<h2 id="algorithm">Algorithm</h2>
<p>Shortest time from X to D</p>
<ol>
  <li>count shortest path â€“&gt; BFS
    <ul>
      <li>shortest path = shortest path of parent +1</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>create queue, enqueue starting position (letâ€™s call it node)
    <ul>
      <li>if X == D, print 0</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>else, loop till the queue is empty
    <ul>
      <li>pop next unvisited node from queue</li>
      <li>If the popped node is destination node, return it</li>
      <li>else, mark current node as visited, and for each of 3 possible movements, enqueue each valid movement into the queue with +1 distance</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr />
<p>header: <iostream>, <queue>,...
array: row=[-1, +1, *2], swap//+x
number line: 0 &lt;=  x, d &lt;= 100,000
how to count steps???// starting point (0) + first shortest path (1) + shortest path from first shortest path (1) +....</queue></iostream></p>

